Shaving down there? Let’s do it right!🐱🪒 

Here’s how to avoid ingrown hair, bumps, and irritation:
	•	Always use fresh razors that are bikini sensitive 
	•  Exfoliate with a gentle face cleanser & gloves to lift your hai
	•	Never dry shave! Apply shaving mousse or gel for a smooth glide
	•	Shave with the hair growth, not against it
	•	Aftercare is key! I use my moisturizer and stick to loose, breathable underwears for a few days 

Still dealing with irritation? DM me, and I’ll help you out!🫶🏻

Darkness around mouth is a lot of people’s insecurity but a proper skincare will definitely improve it and what’s better than making it at home? This is the best DIY mask for it💗💗💗

Causes of darkness around mouth👇🏻

1. Hyperpigmentation (melasma)
2. Friction (lip licking, shaving, waxing)
3. Dryness
4. Sun exposure
5. Vitamin deficiency (B12, iron, folic acid)
6. Allergic reactions (toothpaste, cosmetics)
7. Hormonal changes
8. Genetics

- Take a shower with warm water to soften the hair and open pores.
- Roll or rub gently
- Works only on fine hair
- Once done, rinse off with cold water and apply a moisturizer🧴

NOTE: if you shave your body the hair growth is hard and it will not pull that out it will only remove fine and soft hair!
